text.paragraph:
The safety and effectiveness of levetiracetam for the treatment of partial-onset seizures in patients 1 month to 16 years of age have been established [see  Clinical Pharmacology (12.3) and 
                           Clinical Studies (14.1)
                           ]. The dosing recommendation in these pediatric patients varies according to age group and is weight-based [see 
                           Dosage and Administration (2.6)
                           ].
